RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 57. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUR CUSTOM DARLING was sharp out of the gates, vied for the lead from in between horses, took control of the pace and raced in the two path, was joined by another foe to the outside, raced in a pair down the back side and through the turn, drifted into the five path entering the upper stretch, pulled away from the others while passing the quarter pole, was under strong encouragement and urging, was able to maintain the lead from the quarte pole to the wire and walked away with the win. SAVANNAH'S HERE vied for the lead, raced in the three path, drew next to the other front runner and set the pace in a set, this pair put some distance between themselves and the rest of the field, these two matched strides through the turn, at the quarter pole SAVANNAH'S HERE retreated from the battle for the win but was able to drive down the stretch and take second place honors today. BEAUTIFULGUATEMALA stalked the two front runners from the four and five paths, shifted into the three path entering the lane, was encouraged and responded well by closing and gaining ground, was with in striking distance but could not get past the winner and just missed for place, settling for the show spot. LOYAL TO THE CHIEF vied for the early lead, settled off of the pace in the two path, saved ground and closed well. DONTFORGETRDREAMS 4w, never involved. DORGENOIS rail, trailed through out.

ENTRY.NAME: Loyal to the Chief
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, settled 2w, saved ground, closed well

ENTRY.NAME: Our Custom Darling
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, led, 2w, pace, 4-5w upper, drifted out, urging, held on

ENTRY.NAME: Savannah's Here
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied, 3w, matched strides, pace, retreated 1/4, held on for 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Beautifulguatemala
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalkd, 4w, 5 wide, upper, shifted into 3pth lane, just missed 2n

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 11000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BELLA'S GATSBY raced well off of the pace and at the back of the field, raced four and five wide while being rated in hands, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, responded well and willingly circled horses through the tun, took command by the quarter pole under slight urging, was under left handed encouragement in the upper stretch, responded well and drew off and won under a hand ride. FIVE O FOX vied for the lead, took control and attended the pace while racing in the three path, was asked to rate for the first half mile, was given rein at the half mile pole, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, was pressured by outside attackers, repelled one of the attackers, let the other one go, was encouraged and driven down the lane under strong urging, was no match for the winner but was second best today. CUNNING stalked from the rail, saved ground through out, had a clean trip, was asked to close and was kept on point, surely gained ground with every stride and was able to secure third. NOBLE CONNECTION raced off of the pace from the four path, steadily gained ground, circled through the turn improved position and was within striking distance then faded. JARED THE WARRIOR raced from off of the pace and made a mild bid, improving position slightly. CHIEF BULLET made no impact. WINNING DANCE forwardly placed, faltered.

ENTRY.NAME: Cunning
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, rail, saved ground, clean trip, closed

ENTRY.NAME: Five O Fox
ENTRY.COMMENT: led, 3w, attended the pace, bid3/8, no match for winner

ENTRY.NAME: Jared the Warrior
ENTRY.OWNER: Tri-Star Racing LLC and Cimarron TTT Farms LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Bella's Gatsby
ENTRY.OWNER: Ramirez Racing and Juarez Munoz Juan Carlos

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs. Accredited Arkansas and Texas Bred Preferred.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FROSTY BREW vied for the lead, took control, set the pace was briefly challenged at the five sixteenth pole by an outside offender, quickly put that one away and went wire to wire un contested. PETULA was off of the pace early in the race, was five wide and outside down the back side, advanced at the half mile pole, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, raced four wide in the turn maintaining position, was urged at the quarter pole, responded well, closed down the stretch ducked in for a stride, was corrected, hooked an outside rival at the eighth mile pole, battled and out finished the rest scoring second place. SMARTY'S ANGEL was three wide and stalking, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, challenged by the five sixteenth pole, battled briefly in the stretch then faltered. WAIT ON ME raced off of the pace, was in the three path and inside of another rival, shifted out at the three eighths pole, was five wide in the turn and six wide in the upper stretch, was asked and responded well to encouragement and closed making a mild bid late. ARKLAHOMA SOUL was no menace. BIDOFHONEY was sharp out of the gate, flashed early speed then gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RISKTAKER was racing in the middle of the field after the break, was three wide and in between foes while gaining ground, steadied slightly nearing the three eighths pole, shifted out into the four path and launched a winning bid, raced past rivals, cleared the front runners by the eighth pole and drew off after the sixteenth under a hand ride. PRICED RIGH Twas reluctant to load. vied for the lead, led the race from the two path, attended the pace, was under pressure and getting strong encouragement at the quarter pole, was cleared by an outside rival by the eighth pole, was no match for that one but continued to run and repelled the other attackers finishing with a hard earned second. OURQUICKDRAWMCGRAW stalked the pace, raced in the two path, saved ground through the turn, slowly but surely gained ground in the stretch, was guided down the lane and encouraged, getting up for third. GTUONE BUCK was off a touch slow, was well off the pace, rallied from the back and quickly gained ground on the outside passing rivals down the back side, was four wide in the turn, was in contention at the quarter pole then tired by the eighth mile pole. MR. BUTCH WOMBLE made no impact. LETSTAKEITOUTSIDE raced on the rail, was off of the pace, and never got involved. NINEJUANJUAN CALL trailed through out.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 5 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For A Claiming Price Of Less Than $25,000). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it wil l be run on the main track at 1 Mile and 70 Yards) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CITY NIGHTS vied for the lead, took the rail, set the pace, was joined by another rival and worked in a set, while setting the fractions, briefly let the rival on the outside of him get his head in front for a call, took advantage of the rail, gained ground on the inside, re captured the lead, shook that rival at the quarter pole, had the lead alone, was pressured by an outside competitor closing in on him, managed to keep a length in front for the last sixteenth and got the win. HE GOTS TO GO stalked the pace in the four path, moved at the half mile pole, circled the field in the turn, loomed up near the leader at the quarter pole but could not over take that rival and settled for second. RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs. Accredited Arkansas and Texas Bred Preferred.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UPTOWN SOCIAL vied for the lead, set the pace from the inside in the two path, showed the way around the track was almost home free but got caught at the wire by an outside rival and dead heated for the win. PREMIUM raced in a stalking position in the second flight of horses, was between foes, advanced after the half mile pole with another rival to his outside, launched a bid in a set on the outside through the turn, caught another rival creating a battle entering the stretch, shook the rival to his o continued down the lane and hooked the early pace setters, engaged in a three way battle, while still chasing the early leader, cleared his two inside foes with only a few strides left to go and nailed the front runner at the wire ending in a dead heat. RUNANDHIDE WIND stalked from the two path, saved ground while racing on the inside of other foes, battled in a three way battle after the sixteenth pole, held on for third. AUX ARCS stalked, raced four wide and on the outside, battled for second place in between to other competitors after the sixteenth pole, then faded in hte last few strides.
